# Read-only: computes and returns the standoff pose (see
# TrajectoryPlanner::planAndExecuteInFrontOf) WITHOUT moving the arm. Lets
# a caller (e.g. a web backend) check whether a deterministic standoff pose
# is available (camera_frame TF resolvable) before deciding whether to
# move there or fall back to a preset pose — see todo.txt item 1.
#
# used_fallback is true when camera_frame TF wasn't available and
# standoff_pose was instead read from the "standoff" entry in
# preset_poses_sim.yaml/_real.yaml (see PresetPoses). success is still
# true in that case — a caller only needs to check used_fallback if it
# cares which source the pose came from. success is false only when
# NEITHER a live TF lookup NOR a "standoff" preset was available.
---
bool success
bool used_fallback
string message
geometry_msgs/Pose standoff_pose